  • Method Details

    • execute

      CommandResult execute(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest req, javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServiceException
      Uses Service objects to execute a specific task using data got from HttpServletRequest and HttpServletResponse objects
      Parameters:
      req - HttpServletRequest, which contains data that needs to be processed
      resp - HttpServletResponse, which can be used to manipulate the response the client receives
      Returns:
      CommandResult object, which field values determine the page to forward/redirect to and whether to forward or redirect
      Throws:
      ServiceException - if a ServiceException is thrown by a Service object's method
